#: ../../source/encryption.rst:4
msgid "OpenModelica Encryption"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/encryption.rst:6
msgid ""
"The encryption module allows the library developers to encrypt their "
"libraries for different platforms. Note that you need a special version "
"of OpenModelica with encryption support. Contact us if you want one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/encryption.rst:11
msgid "Encrypting the Library"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/encryption.rst:13
msgid ""
"In order to encrypt the Modelica package call "
"`buildEncryptedPackage(TopLevelPackageName)` from mos script or from "
"**OMEdit** right click the package in Libraries Browser and select "
"`Export Encrypted Package` or select `Export > Export Encrypted Package` "
"from the menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/encryption.rst:18
msgid ""
"All the Modelica files are encrypted and the whole library is zipped into"
" a single file i.e., `PackageName.mol`. Note that you can only encrypt "
"Modelica packages saved in a folder structure. The complete folder "
"structure remains as it is. No encryption is done on the resource files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/encryption.rst:24
msgid "Loading an Encrypted Library"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/encryption.rst:26
msgid ""
"To load the encrypted package call "
"`loadEncryptedPackage(EncryptedPackage.mol)` from the mos script or from "
"**OMEdit** `File > Load Encrypted Package`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/encryption.rst:30
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/encryption.rst:32
msgid ""
"There is no license management and obfuscation of the generated code and "
"files. However just a basic encryption and decryption is supported along "
"with full support for protection access annotation as defined in Modelica"
" specification 18.9. This means that anyone who has an OpenModelica "
"version with encryption support can encrypt or decrypt files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/encryption.rst:38
msgid ""
"OpenModelica encryption is based on SEMLA (Safe/Superiour/Super "
"Encryption of Modelica Libraries and Artifacts) module from Modelon AB."
msgstr ""

